snippet.textDisplay:
Here’s why the SARS-COV-II is so much worse than the regular Flu:
1. It’s NOVEL meaning there is no previous immunity in humans - therefore the chain of contagion is linear (no skipping) when infection begins & this makes it a super fast spreader
2. The R-Naught is at least 100% increase over the flu which is around 1.x (That’s with moderate estimates of 2.2R0 when in fact it’s likely to be 4.x+).
3. Inoculations estimated earliest next year (and are they even safe if they’re rushed?)
4. It attacks very low in the lung and this creates a higher CFR than the average flu(0.1%) (30-40% pts need supplemental Oxygen & an average US hospital has only <= 100 Oxygen respirators). CFR for SARS-COV-II is 2.1% avg {2000% increase}
5. R-Naught increases with poor healthcare and healthcare can become poor if it becomes over stressed by the vast number of cases.
6. Asymptomatic infection & mean incubation time being 12.5 up to 28 days.
STOCK UP ON EVERYTHING. Also we need to hold China accountable for the perpetual an ongoing emergence of these diseases in their horrible wetmarkets, hygiene, etc.

snippet.textDisplay:
Students at 15 Taiwanese universities have established Falun Dafa clubs in which they do the meditation exercises and introduce the practice to other people on campus.

These schools include Taiwan University, National Taiwan Normal University, National Taiwan University of Science and Technology, The Chinese Culture University, National Taiwan University of Arts, National Chengchi University (NCCU), National Tsing Hua University, National Chiao Tung University, National Central University, National Chung Hsing University, National Chiayi University, National Chung Cheng University, TransWorld University, National Yunlin University of Science and Technology, and National Cheng Kung University.


Members of the National Chengchi University Falun Dafa club set up a booth on the campus grounds to introduce the meditation practice to students.

The Falun Dafa club at National Chengchi University (NCCU) hosts a booth at the beginning of every semester so that students and faculty members can get to know the practice better.

Sena, an international student from Turkey, is studying psychology at NCCU. She was introduced to Falun Dafa through the club's information booth and wanted to take up the meditation discipline. She signed up for some activities the club was holding for new students and learned the five sets of Falun Dafa exercises.
